<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-03-09T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-03-09T19:00:00-05:00" n="400" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/3–550: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Legation in Jordan</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-03-09T19:00:00-05:00">March
                                        9, 1950—7 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>24. Ur 38 Mar 5 and previous. Dept disappointed by recent
                                developments culminating in setback for King in his efforts bring
                                conversations with Israel to concrete conclusion. If you believe
                                such action wld be helpful, you are authorized convey to King an
                                expression of Dept’s appreciation for efforts he has so far made on
                                behalf peace and stability in Palestine, and of Dept’s hope that
                                King will continue seek agreement. You might refer to President’s
                                msg of encouragement to King sent <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 216 Dec 30, 1949.<note n="1" xml:id="d400fn1">This message gave the text of President Truman’s message to
                                    King Abdullah; see <ref target="frus1949v06#pg_1564">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1949, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">vi</hi>, p. 1564</ref>.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>In your discretion you are also authorized discreetly to encourage
                                members of Jordan Govt re desirability of continuing conversations
                                with Israelis in effort arrive at satisfactory formula for
                                agreement.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>